149
00:05:34,530 --> 00:05:36,270
- How did you actually
build that business out?

150
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:37,470
Where did it all start from?

151
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:39,994
- I started making free
videos for lots of people-

152
00:05:39,994 --> 00:05:41,730
- Hang on, hang on, did you say free?

153
00:05:41,730 --> 00:05:42,870
What, you didn't charge people?

154
00:05:42,870 --> 00:05:43,703
- No, I didn't.

155
00:05:43,703 --> 00:05:45,540
At the start when you are
trying to build your skills

156
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:47,550
as a videographer, which is what I was,

157
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:50,130
no one really trusts you and
doesn't really wanna pay you

158
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:51,450
if they haven't seen what you've done,

159
00:05:51,450 --> 00:05:53,280
so you have to build up a portfolio.

160
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:55,560
So I did everything from wedding videos,

161
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,090
to shooting club videos.

162
00:05:57,090 --> 00:06:00,690
- So how'd you go about going
from a very small startup,

163
00:06:00,690 --> 00:06:02,970
giving away free content,

164
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:05,640
to actually having people on your staff,

165
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,110
as it were, being a real company.

166
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:08,700
- So it's all about niching down.

167
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:09,533
And then when you niche,

168
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:11,910
and become an expert in your
field, you can charge more.

169
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:14,190
- Lots of people think
that by doing everything,

170
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:15,930
you have a much wider market.

171
00:06:15,930 --> 00:06:18,780
And although this is true to some extent,

172
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:23,040
would you rather be operated
on by a surgeon or a GP?

173
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:26,340
I can guarantee that you
chose surgeon, but why?

174
00:06:26,340 --> 00:06:29,790
Naturally, we feel safer
in the hands of an expert,

175
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:32,520
and this is the same
across all aspects of life.

176
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:35,310
So my advice on how to
become an expert would be,

177
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:37,440
number one, find your niche.

178
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,720
You need to find a niche that has demand,

179
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,340
which you can add value to.

180
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:44,310
Number two, gain practical experience.

181
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:47,700
Try to experience different
areas within your chosen niche

182
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:50,070
to gain a wide range of skills.

183
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:52,500
Number three, continuously learn.

184
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:53,880
You need to stay updated

185
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,430
with trends and developments
within your niche.

186
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:58,200
Don't be late to the party.

187
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:01,260
And number four, build
a professional network.

188
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,780
There's one thing better
than being an expert,

189
00:07:03,780 --> 00:07:06,960
and that's being an expert
with expert friends.

190
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:10,260
The staff was starting to
