We landed in Miami, and I spent the week

258
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:11,370
meeting up with some great
people like Patrick Bet-David,

259
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:14,760
Luke Belmar, Grant
Cardone, and Ben Marler.

260
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:17,160
But the most exciting for me was John Fox,

261
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:21,780
he invited me to a private
airport to fly one of his planes.

262
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:24,060
I must admit, I did hesitate a little,

263
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:27,000
I hadn't flown a plane
for around 15 years.

264
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,430
Not only was this guy a plane expert,

265
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:31,230
but he was a pro flyer,

266
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:33,810
and I was worried I
wouldn't be as good as I was

267
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:37,320
when I last flew with
him over 30 years ago.

268
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,840
What piece of advice would you
give to a youngster nowadays

269
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:42,570
if they wanted to own a
beautiful aircraft like this?

270
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:46,740
- Go out there and try
everything you think you want.

271
00:10:46,740 --> 00:10:50,430
Try everything you
think you're gonna love,

272
00:10:50,430 --> 00:10:52,770
and try some of the things
that you don't like,

273
00:10:52,770 --> 00:10:55,080
and you'll surprise your inner heart,

274
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:59,190
and something will spark,
and then follow that path.

275
00:10:59,190 --> 00:11:01,200
- Well, I think that's very
sound advice my friend.

276
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:04,050
- I'm gonna certify
that, did you get that?

277
00:11:04,050 --> 00:11:07,350
- With that said, it was time
for me to pursue my passion

278
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:09,240
and take to the skies.

279
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:12,360
Evaluating the risks was
the last thing on my mind,

280
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:15,510
flying planes is what
sets my soul on fire.

281
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:17,070
And deep down I knew that

282
00:11:17,070 --> 00:11:19,080
if I didn't seize this opportunity,

283
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,680
I would forever wonder, what if?

284
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:23,552
♪ You gotta give all you got ♪

285
00:11:23,552 --> 00:11:27,242
♪ Gotta give all you've got for love ♪

286
00:11:27,242 --> 00:11:29,511
♪ 'Cause you're here for a moment ♪

287
00:11:29,511 --> 00:11:33,033
♪ Give all you've got, gotta
give all you've got for love ♪

288
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:36,742
♪ Give all you've got, give
all you've got for love ♪

289
00:11:36,742 --> 00:11:37,700
- Absolutely fantastic.

290
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,700
I'm a bit emotional
actually, to be honest.

291
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:41,112
- [John] That's okay.

292
00:11:41,112 --> 00:11:43,695
(gentle music)

